The paper presents a novel approach to collaborative filtering, which is a subfield of information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed approach involves clustering and similarity measures, which are also relevant to data science (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the limitations of existing CF algorithms, which is a topic of interest in social and information networks (cs.SI).
